Description:
Incorrect or missing validation for dashboard status indicators.
The Explore Dashboard feature fails to validate and accurately display the status of key items (e.g., expense claims, tasks, or reports). This leads to misleading or inconsistent status information being shown to users.

Creator: Ruthwik Mamidala
Description:
Issues in Approval Delegation: delegated approvals are not correctly handled, leading to workflow disruptions.

When an approval task is delegated to another user, the system fails to assign the task accurately or notify the delegate. This results in tasks being missed, delayed, or incorrectly executed, disrupting the approval workflow.

Creator: Ruthwik Mamidala
Description:
Notification failures observed during the Approval Process: alerts and updates not sent to relevant stakeholders.

The Approval Process does not reliably trigger notifications (emails, in-app alerts, or push notifications) to the designated stakeholders (e.g., approvers or requesters). This inconsistency causes delays and confusion in the workflow.

Creator: Ruthwik Mamidala
Description:
Field validation issues in the Approval Process: mandatory fields are not correctly validated during submission.

During the Approval Process, certain required fields (e.g., "Approver Name," "Approval Date," or "Comments") are not being properly validated. Users can proceed without providing necessary inputs, leading to incomplete or erroneous approval submissions.

Summary: Delete Purchase Order - Data Flow-Out Testing
Creator: Ruthwik Mamidala
Description:
Data Flow-Out issues observed when deleting a Purchase Order: downstream systems are not updated or notified.
When a Purchase Order is deleted, the system fails to propagate this change to downstream systems or modules that rely on this data (e.g., inventory, accounts payable, or reporting modules). This leads to inconsistencies across integrated systems.

Summary: Delete Purchase Order - Data Dependency Validation "Order Number" and "Status"
Creator: Ruthwik Mamidala
Description:
Inconsistent behavior observed when deleting a Purchase Order: status dependency with "Order Number" not handled properly.

When attempting to delete a Purchase Order, the system does not validate the relationship between the "Order Number" and its associated "Status."
